$>mkvirtualenv mynewproject
Creates a new virtual environment in $WORKON_HOME, which is defined in .bash_profile in ~/user/<username>/.bash_profile

$>deactivate
Shut-down a currently active virtual environment

$>mkproject mynewproject
Creates a new directory named mynewproject at $PROJECT_HOME, which is defined in .bash_profile, and sets pwd to mynewproject.

$>workon
Lists out virtual envs available

$>workon <environment name>
Changes to <environment name>

$>rmvirtualenv <environment name>
The <environment name> must be deactivated before it can be removed.
